ENVIRONMENT DIVISION.
CONFIGURATION SECTION.
INPUT-OUTPUT SECTION.
FILE-CONTROL.
    SELECT INPUT-FILE ASSIGN TO 'INPUT.DAT'
     ORGANIZATION IS LINE SEQUENTIAL.
    SELECT OUTPUT-FILE ASSIGN TO 'OUTPUT.DAT'
     ORGANIZATION IS LINE SEQUENTIAL.

DATA DIVISION.
FILE SECTION.
FD  INPUT-FILE.
01  INPUT-RECORD PIC X(80).

FD  OUTPUT-FILE.
01  OUTPUT-RECORD PIC X(80).

WORKING-STORAGE SECTION.
01  FRODO-VARIABLE PIC 9(4) VALUE 0.
01  SAMWISE-VARIABLE PIC 9(4) VALUE 0.
01  GANDALF-VARIABLE PIC 9(4) VALUE 0.
01  TEMP-VARIABLE PIC X(80).
01  MICKEY-MOUSE PIC X(80).
01  DONALD-DUCK PIC X(80).
01  BUGS-BUNNY PIC X(80).

PROCEDURE DIVISION.
MAIN-PROCEDURE.
    OPEN INPUT INPUT-FILE
    OPEN OUTPUT OUTPUT-FILE
    PERFORM READ-INPUT-FILE
    PERFORM PROCESS-RECORDS
    PERFORM WRITE-OUTPUT-FILE
    CLOSE INPUT-FILE
    CLOSE OUTPUT-FILE
    STOP RUN.

READ-INPUT-FILE.
    READ INPUT-FILE INTO TEMP-VARIABLE
     AT END MOVE 'EOF' TO TEMP-VARIABLE
    END-READ.

PROCESS-RECORDS.
    MOVE TEMP-VARIABLE TO MICKEY-MOUSE
    MOVE MICKEY-MOUSE TO DONALD-DUCK
    MOVE DONALD-DUCK TO BUGS-BUNNY
    ADD 1 TO FRODO-VARIABLE
    ADD 2 TO SAMWISE-VARIABLE
    ADD 3 TO GANDALF-VARIABLE.

WRITE-OUTPUT-FILE.
    MOVE BUGS-BUNNY TO OUTPUT-RECORD
    WRITE OUTPUT-RECORD.

